## Playbooks

Per-type methodology lives in `methodology/<type>.md`. AIDEX ships with six stock playbooks:

| Type | File | When to run |
|---|---|---|
| UX audit | [methodology/ux-audit.md](methodology/ux-audit.md) | Pre-release, UX drift suspected |
| AI opportunities | [methodology/ia-opportunities.md](methodology/ia-opportunities.md) | New AI capability scope, phase end |
| Re-test | [methodology/retest.md](methodology/retest.md) | After a batch of P0/P1 fixes |
| Security audit | [methodology/security-audit.md](methodology/security-audit.md) | Fixed cadence or post sensitive feature |
| Performance audit | [methodology/perf-audit.md](methodology/perf-audit.md) | Pre-release, pre-scaling |
| Accessibility audit | [methodology/a11y-audit.md](methodology/a11y-audit.md) | Compliance cadence |

Only the playbooks you've actually used are present. `/audit new <type> <slug>` materializes one on first use.

